title: S. Jersey Girls: S.J. girls: Moorestown rallies past Eustace in Coaches Tournament
text:
More coverage: Southeastern Pa. high school sports Miranda Sackner's hat trick helped host Cinnaminson power past Burlington Township, 5-1. Cinnaminson is ranked No. 10 in South Jersey by The Inquirer.
Morgan Ryan and Brianna Taylor each had a goal and an assist to lead Delran to a 4-1 home win over Northern Burlington. 
Jenna Dobbins scored the winner as visiting Medford Tech beat Florence, 1-0, in double overtime. 
Madison Conroy, Lily Garrett, and Madison Hartman each scored for Palmyra in its 3-0 victory at Willingboro. 
Olympic Conference. Emily Gray scored twice and Kylie D'Ambra also tallied as No. 5 Washington Township rallied to defeat No. 4 Cherokee, 3-2, in overtime. 
Tziarra King scored twice as Winslow Township tied host Seneca, 3-3. Brianna Breen stopped 13 shots for the visitors. 
Kayla DeGuzman and Roni Schaffer scored and Cherry Hill East defeated host Cherry Hill West, 2-1. Alexa Beatty had an assist. 
Colonial Conference. Madison Blanda, Taylor Carmack, Kiersten Pease, and Justina Snyder scored for host Haddon Heights in its 4-0 victory over Lindenwold. Pease also had an assist. 
Bailey Adolf made 10 saves for Sterling, which drew West Deptford, 1-1, at home. Maggie David stopped nine shots for the visitors. 
Cape-Atlantic League. Amanda Durbin, Jenna Durbin, and Marissa McGaffney scored and Lower Cape May won at Atlantic County Tech, 3-1. Marissa Giancola stopped seven shots for the visitors. Girls' Tennis Moorestown defeated Mainland, 5-0, in the state Group 3 semifinals at Mercy County Park, but saw its season end with a 4-1 defeat to Millburn in the final.
First singles player Emily O'Neil won, 7-5, 6-3, to lead the Quakers past Mainland. 
Alex Boone and Camilla Hox de Vila won, 3-6, 6-2, (10-6) against Milburn at first doubles. 
State Group 4 Semifinals. Stephanie Yanosov won, 6-1, 6-0, at first singles, but Cherry Hill East fell to Montgomery, 3-2. 
State Group 1 Semifinals. First doubles team Haley Kircher and Aimee Ridgeway won, 4-6, 6-4, (10-7), but Pennsville fell to Shore Regional, 4-1. Field Hockey Carley Dluoik scored on a pass from Shania Miller in the first half and host Deptford defeated Highland, 1-0, in a nonleague match.
Tolu Gureje stopped five shots.
